<paragraph id="E97036DD3F75FFE2FF76FEA4FD26FEDD" blockId="64.[151,1437,290,893]" box="[151,710,290,317]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Size. Known adult size about 
<quantity id="2E379B383F75FFE2FE07FEA4FDD9FEDD" box="[486,569,290,317]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="cm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 cm</quantity>
total length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F75FFE2FF26FEC0FD1FFC9D" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F75FFE2FF26FEC0FAEEFE2D" blockId="64.[151,1437,290,893]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Morphology. D VI + I,11–13; A I,11–13; P 15–18. Short and stout body, nearly cylindrical, except for laterally compressed caudal peduncle (Kovačić 2006). Caudal peduncle slender, lower than body. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first with a more or less rounded edge. Caudal fin truncate to slightly emarginate. Body and predorsal area covered with scales (Miller 1986), usually poorly visible on live specimen photographs (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F75FFE2FB4CFE34FAE0FE2D" box="[1197,1280,434,460]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,2004,2028]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,1136,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-42@17.[161,1427,1136,1979]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius vittatus. Photo by S.V. Bogorodsky, Turkey, Aegean Sea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601593/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F75FFE2FF26FE50FE5DFD61" blockId="64.[151,1437,290,893]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Live coloration. Background coloration pale to white, light yellow or beige, with 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F75FFE2FB89FE50FB50FDF5" bold="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">a broad, dark-chestnut to black stripe between the upper lip and snout and the caudal fin, passing through the eyes</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F75FFE2FB5FFE7CFAF1FDF5" box="[1214,1297,506,532]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,2004,2028]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,1136,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-42@17.[161,1427,1136,1979]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius vittatus. Photo by S.V. Bogorodsky, Turkey, Aegean Sea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601593/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). The lateral stripes of both sides meet above the upper lip, forming a V-shaped snout line that slightly extends onto mid upper lip (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F75FFE2FF25FDC4FEF8FDBD" box="[196,280,578,604]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,2004,2028]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,1136,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-42@17.[161,1427,1136,1979]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius vittatus. Photo by S.V. Bogorodsky, Turkey, Aegean Sea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601593/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Fins mostly clear and unmarked, yet often with a light pink hue on the rays and membranes (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F75FFE2FAA3FDC4FA74FDBD" box="[1346,1428,578,604]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,2004,2028]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,1136,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-42@17.[161,1427,1136,1979]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius vittatus. Photo by S.V. Bogorodsky, Turkey, Aegean Sea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601593/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F75FFE2FF7EFDE0FE51FD61" author="Heymer, A. &amp; Zander, C. D." box="[159,433,614,640]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="132 - 143" refId="ref56256" refString="Heymer, A. &amp; Zander, C. D. (1978) Morphology and ecology of Gobius vittatus and its possible mimicry relationship to Blennius rouxi in the Mediterranean. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolution, 16, 132 - 143. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1439 - 0469.1978. tb 00925. x" type="journal article" year="1978">Heymer &amp; Zander 1978</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F75FFE2FF26FD0CFB83FD45" blockId="64.[151,1437,290,893]" box="[199,1123,650,676]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F75FFE2FE9EFD0CFD25FD45" box="[383,709,650,676]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Callionymidae" genus="Tridentriger" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trigonocephalus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F75FFE2FE9EFD0CFD25FD45" box="[383,709,650,676]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Tridentriger trigonocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also the blenny 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F75FFE2FC65FD0CFB83FD45" box="[900,1123,650,676]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F75FFE2FC65FD0CFB80FD45" baseAuthorityName="Cocco" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[900,1120,650,676]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Blenniidae" genus="Parablennius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rouxi">Parablennius rouxi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F75FFE2FF26FD28FBDCFCF1" blockId="64.[151,1437,290,893]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Habitat. Infralittoral and circalittoral species, known from 
<quantity id="2E379B383F75FFE2FCB8FD28FC4FFD29" box="[857,943,686,713]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="m" value="43.5" valueMax="85.0" valueMin="2.0">2–85 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F75FFE2FBE2FD28FB0DFD29" author="Francour, P. &amp; Bodilis, P. &amp; Cottalorda, J. M. &amp; Seytre, C." box="[1027,1261,686,712]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref54712" refString="Francour, P., Bodilis, P., Cottalorda, J. M. &amp; Seytre, C. (2010) Inventaire des Gobiidae dans la Reiserve Naturelle de Scandola (Corse) et aI proximitei de ses limites. Contrat Parc Naturel Reigional de la Corse. Universitei de Nice-Sophia Antipolis, ECOMERS publ., Nice, 1 - 54." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Francour 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F75FFE2FB93FD29FB43FD29" box="[1138,1187,686,712]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
), most frequent between 
<quantity id="2E379B383F75FFE2FF1FFD54FE83FD0D" box="[254,355,722,749]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="m" value="27.5" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="15.0">15–40 m</quantity>
depth, on steep to moderate rocky slopes made of boulders or coralligenous beds (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F75FFE2FAC0FD54FEC8FCF1" author="Heymer, A. &amp; Zander, C. D." pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="132 - 143" refId="ref56256" refString="Heymer, A. &amp; Zander, C. D. (1978) Morphology and ecology of Gobius vittatus and its possible mimicry relationship to Blennius rouxi in the Mediterranean. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolution, 16, 132 - 143. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1439 - 0469.1978. tb 00925. x" type="journal article" year="1978">Heymer &amp; Zander 1978</bibRefCitation>
), more rarely on sand (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F75FFE2FDCAFD70FD2DFCF1" author="Kovacic, M." box="[555,717,758,784]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" refId="ref57856" refString="Kovacic, M. (2004) Biolos ˇ ka i ekolos ˇ ka obiljez ˇ ja vrste Gobius vittatus (Gobiidae, Pisces) u Jadranskom moru. PhD Dissertation, University of Zagreb, Zagreb, 178 pp." type="book" year="2004">Kovačić 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F75FFE2FD36FD70FBD0FCF1" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Arko-Pijevac, M." box="[727,1072,758,784]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="39 - 45" refId="ref58330" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Arko-Pijevac, M. (2008) Habitat preferences, distribution, and abundance of Gobius vittatus (Gobiidae) in the Kvarner area (Northern Adriatic Sea). Vie et Milieu, 58, 39 - 45." type="journal article" year="2008">Kovačić &amp; Arko-Pijevac 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F75FFE2FF26FC9CFD1FFC9D" blockId="64.[151,1437,290,893]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Geographic distribution. Northern Mediterranean, presently known from the Strait of 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F75FFE2FB4DFC9CFAF1FCD5" box="[1196,1297,794,820]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
in Spain to Leghorn in 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F75FFE2FEF8FCB8FEADFCB9" box="[281,333,830,856]" name="Italy" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Italy</collectingCountry>
, in the Gulf of Taranto and the Gargano Peninsula (
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F75FFE2FC6DFCB8FC24FCB8" box="[908,964,830,857]" name="Italy" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Italy</collectingCountry>
), Eastern Adriatic, the Aegean Sea (Miller 1986). Also recorded from Crete (Kovačić 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F75FFE2FD99FCE5FD4AFC9D" box="[632,682,866,892]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">et al</emphasis>
. 2011).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
